    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f1ec3268_d7e9568b",
        "filename": "util/linux/scoped_ptrace_attach.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 53,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-07T01:40:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e If any of these three happen, should we Reset()? (I assume that we’d still want to detach or try to detach in these cases, but again, a look at the kernel source would be helpful.)\n\u003e \n\u003e If we do want to Reset(), we should merge things a bit to share code in the status-checkers, since the LOG is the only thing that’d differ:\n\u003e \n\u003e   if (!stopped) {\n\u003e     if (exited || signaled) {\n\u003e       LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"process exited\";\n\u003e     } else {\n\u003e       LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"process not stopped\";\n\u003e     }\n\u003e     Reset();\n\u003e     return false;\n\u003e   }\n\n(Might be enough to just check !WIFSTOPPED, though, and not break it out further. Should be unlikely, right? Your call.)",
      "parentUuid": "71e7f1be_107e93b8",
      "revId": "039c5b2c5406306c482b6728a1087b4c0d748272",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2f926dbf_c1fb7b2b",
        "filename": "util/linux/scoped_ptrace_attach.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 53,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-07T18:48:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, it looks like WIFEXITED, WIFSTOPPED, and WIFSIGNALED are mutually exclusive.\nI just check for stopped now.\n\nIf the tracee has exited or been killed, then PTRACE_DETACH should fail with ESRCH.\nA Reset/Detach shouldn\u0027t be necessary, but should also be safe to try.\nIt will currently be attempted on destruction since pid_ has already been set.",
      "parentUuid": "f1ec3268_d7e9568b",
      "revId": "039c5b2c5406306c482b6728a1087b4c0d748272",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
